36 Watercolor Pencils in Gift Box (Includes water brush and small water cup)

Break Resistant Leads

Secural bonding process (SV) strengthens leads to resist breakage, while providing sharp fine lines and excellent point retention.

  • Thick 3.8 mm leads
  • Break-resistant
  • Water-soluble
  • Fade resistant

Faber-Castell Albrecht Durer Artists' Watercolor Pencils

36 Watercolor Pencils in Studio Gift Box

The Albrecht Durer artists watercolor pencil has been prized for many years by creative minds all over the world for its exceptional properties. Trusted by professional artists as the finest quality watercolor pencils available.

  • Premium artist quality, made in Germany
  • Fully water-soluble leads
  • Smooth color stroke
  • Studio Gift Box includes water brush and small water cup
  • Consistent color when wet or dry
  • Unsurpassed lightfastness (resistance to fading)
  • Colors become permanent when dry
Read more
Read more

Premium Artist Quality Watercolor Pencils

High-quality materials, combined with over 250 years of experience, have resulted in watercolor pencils that produce unsurpassed watercolor effects and vibrancy. The colored surface can be transformed with only a few fine or broad brush strokes to reveal the full and unique power of the colors.

Depending on the paper being used, pigments can be completely dissolved, and will then behave in the same way as classic watercolor paints.

      anonymau5
      5.0 out of 5 stars True artist quality materials.
      Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2013
      Style: Studio box.Size: 36erVerified Purchase
      I'm just a hobby-level artist trying to branch to different media. I prefer sketching and charcoal but have wanted to try out watercoloring and these pencils seemed to be a logical progression.

      I'm no expert by any means but will try to point out the best qualities of these pencils.

      First off is that the colors are incredibly vibrant and look amazing on paper. The pigment completely dissolves when a wet brush is applied and the pigment can be pulled from the pencils themselves using a brush and applied directly to the paper. Obviously you can use them dry and they react like soft core colored pencils. If you use a wet application after though you can't tell pencil was used as the colors are completely dissolved. The colors are permanent though once dried which is great because it allows for more layering.

      I sharpened them by hand to expose roughly twice as much of the cores then with a traditional sharpener so I can use them for burnishing easier and also to pull color from the core using a brush directly. The cores are holding up incredibly well, I have no fear of them breaking even with almost a full inch exposed.

      Another small note worth mentioning is the quality of wood used as well was apparent to me when sharpening. The wood actually cut away and was soft enough that it wasn't a huge hassle to sharpen all 36 of them by hand. A small point obviously but I felt worth mentioning.

      The case itself is nice, I chose this over the tin to shave a couple bucks off and I liked how the gift box looked. The flap that opens also has a magnet in it to shut the box together and can be used as a stand.

      The only downside is of course lack of colors. Not that the set is lacking per se but some colors are missing. Examples are lack of flesh tones, greys and browns. Jerry's Artrama supply (spelling) here on Amazon sells the individual pencils as well but you'll need to do a bit of searching to find them. I'm supplementing this set with about 20 pinks, browns, fleshes and greys.

      I'll be adding some pictures soon. Need to paint some examples and also waiting on a paper block to be delivered.

      If you want actual artist quality watercolor pencils then the Albrecht Durer line is what you want. They're fantastic.

I find that the pencils sharpened very easily and with the correct sharpener you don't waste very much at all. The lines are smooth and the colors are very vibrant which I like very much. I thought maybe this would be messy but I use a water brush and it makes everything perfect so I can do this sitting down in my couch and I can get up at a moment's notice and not spell or have to worry about anything getting all over the place. I am so happy with this product and can't wait to order those larger set.

      L200911
      5.0 out of 5 stars Professional Quality
      Reviewed in the United Kingdom on May 8, 2018
      Style: Studio box.Size: 36erVerified Purchase
      Absolutely fantastic. I have tried a few other well known brands when it comes to water colours but as always Faber-Castell out does all of them by miles.
      These are by far the best watercolour Pencils that I have used in my work. Colour lay down is excellent and the pencils feel lovely against both watercolour and mixed media paper. The addition of water serves to intensify each and every colour and it spreads well enough that you could even create washes with them.
      Colour can also be used directly from the pencil with a brush or as indicated in the very informative leaflet contained you can shave some of the colour into a palette and add water to create a more traditional paint style colour.
      They are beautifully presented in a very sturdy case which of course is the signature green with gold embossed lettering which we all associate with quite possibly the best artist brand out there and one that you can definitely trust every time.
      The case also includes a Faber-Castell number 6 brush.
      There is certainly no disappointment with these pencils and they are a fantastic price. I will however be saving to purchase the full set as soon as possible.
